t Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["Probably the most successful of all the Old French names of Germanic origin that were introduced to England by the Normans. It is derived from Germanic <i>wil</i> ‘will, desire’ + <i>helm</i> ‘helmet, protection’. The fact that it was borne by the Conqueror himself does not seem to have inhibited its favour with the ‘conquered’ population: in the first century after the Conquest it was the commonest male name of all, and not only among the Normans. In the later Middle Ages it was overtaken by   John  , but continued to run second to that name until the 20th century, when the picture became more fragmented."],"variants":[]}],"lifeSummary":"When William Malet was born about 1206, in Enmore, Somerset, England, United Kingdom, his father, William Malet III, was 29 and his mother, Sara Sulley, was 32. He had at least 2 sons and 1 daughter with Mrs. Maria Mallet. He died after 1264, in England, United Kingdom."},"et":{"about 1206–after 1264":"umbes 1206–pärast 1264","1206–1264":"1206–1264","1208–Female":"1208–Surnud","1210–Male":"1210–Surnud","1210–Female":"1210–Surnud","1232–Male":"1232–Surnud","1236–Female":"1236–Surnud","1245–1279":"1245–1279","1178–1256":"1178–1256","1176–Female":"1176–Surnud","1176":"1176","1264":"1264","Abt 1236":"umbes 1236","1206":"1206","1215":"1215","1236":"1236","about 1206":"umbes 1206","1279":"1279","1256":"1256","1245":"1245","1178":"1178","1232":"1232","1210":"1210","about 1245":"umbes 1245","after 1264":"pärast 1264","about 1232":"umbes 1232","1208":"1208","Somerset, England":"Somerset, Inglismaa, United Kingdom","England":"Inglismaa, United Kingdom","Enmore, Bridgewater, Somerset, England":"Enmore, Somerset, Inglismaa, United Kingdom","Enmore, Somerset, England":"Enmore, Somerset, England"},"fi":{"about 1206–after 1264":"noin 1206–1264 jälkeen","1206–1264":"1206–1264","1208–Female":"1208–Kuollut","1210–Male":"1210–Kuollut","1210–Female":"1210–Kuollut","1232–Male":"1